Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Mix crumbs and butter; press firmly onto bottom of 8- or 9-inch baking pan. Beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended. Add eggs; mix just until blended. Pour over crust. Bake 40 minutes or until center is almost set. Cool. Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight. Cut into 16 bars. Store leftover bars in refrigerator.